author: Slidebean
description:
Why AI powered weapons still aren’t ready for prime time.

Defense startups like Anduril are positioning AI as faster and more reliable than human operators. But recent Navy tests of autonomous drone vessels revealed critical failures and safety concerns.

In military systems, success isn’t measured by innovation speed, it’s measured by consistency and trust under pressure.
Until AI systems can meet that standard without exception, human oversight remains non negotiable.

title: AI weapons failed a Navy test and that’s a big problem.
